-- Copper Falls 0.5% to $7,217 a Ton in London; Aluminum, Tin Drop
-- B y   D a n   W e e k s
-- 2013-10-15T09:23:30Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2013-10-15/copper-falls-0-5-to-7-217-a-ton-in-london-aluminum-tin-drop.html
Copper for delivery in three months
fell 0.5 percent to $7,217 a metric ton on the London Metal
Exchange. Aluminum and tin slid as lead rose, while nickel and
zinc were little changed.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Dan Weeks at 
 dweeks1@bloomberg.net  